definition.val: A monogenic disease that has_material_basis_in muations in genes on the X chromosome.

A disease of anatomical entity which occurs in the blood, heart, blood vessels or the lymphatic system that passes nutrients (such as amino acids and electrolytes), gases, hormones, blood cells or lymph to and from cells in the body to help fight diseases and help stabilize body temperature and pH to maintain homeostasis.

synonyms.val: disease of subdivision of hemolymphoid system

definition.val: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in endocrine glands which secretes a type of hormone directly into the bloodstream to regulate the body.
A monogenic disease that is has material basis in a mutation in a single gene on one of the non-sex chromosomes.
A monogenic disease that has_material_basis_in muations on the Y chromosome.
A genetic disease associated with mutations encoding defective proteins, which result in either abnormal function formation or function of cilia.
An organ system cancer located_in the thoracic cavity that develops in the different types of cells within the lungs, as well as less common cancers of the esophagus, the trachea, or the chest wall.
A genetic disease that is characterized by underdevelopment of the tips of fingers or toes, underdevelopment or abscense of finger or toe nails and developmental disability.
A monogenic disease that is characterized by glomerulonephritis, endstage kidney disease, and hearing loss.
An acquired metabolic disease that is characterized by abnormal carbohydrate metabolism.
A disease characterized by a group of signs and symptoms that occur together and characterize a particular abnormality.
An organ system cancer that is located in the peritoneum.
A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the central nervous system or located_in the peripheral nervous system.
A disease of anatomical entity that has_material_basis_in hematopoietic cells.

synonyms.val: DISEASE OF THE BLOOD AND BLOOD-FORMING ORGANS

definition.val: A cancer that is classified by the type of cell from which it is derived.
A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body, which do not invade or destroy the surrounding tissue but, given enough time, will transform into a cancer.

A genetic disease that is characterized by slow growth before and after birth, intellectual disability that is usually severe to profound, skeletal abnormalities involving the arms and hands, and distinctive facial features.

basicPropertyValues.val:
Xref MGI.
OMIM mapping confirmed by DO. [SN].

definition.val: A genetic disease that has_material_basis_in mutations in the MODY genes disrupting insulin production.

basicPropertyValues.val:
Xref MGI.
OMIM mapping confirmed by DO. [SN].

definition.val: A genetic disease that is characterized by malformations of the face, oral cavity, and digits.

basicPropertyValues.val:
Xref MGI.
OMIM mapping confirmed by DO. [SN].

definition.val: An organ system cancer located_in the retroperitoneal space that is manifested in retroperitoneal space in the abdominal cavity behind the peritoneum.

synonyms.val: malignant tumor of peritoneum and retroperitoneum
malignant neoplasm of retroperitoneum and peritoneum

definition.val: A genetic disease that is characterized by a drastic and uncontrolled increase in skeletal muscle oxidative metabolism, which overwhelms the body's capacity to supply oxygen, remove carbon dioxide, and regulate body temperature.

basicPropertyValues.val:
Xref MGI.
OMIM mapping confirmed by DO. [SN].

definition.val: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body which lack the ability to metastasize.
An organ system cancer located_in the nervous system that affects the central or peripheral nervous system.
A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the gastrointestinal tract.

A genetic disease that is characterized by permanently bent fingers (camptodactyly), short stature, rocker-bottom or club feet, joints that are bent in a fixed position (contractures), union or webbing of the skin between the fingers (syndactyly), and/or webbing of the neck, inside bend of the elbows, back of the knees and armpits.

A disease that involves a psychological or behavioral pattern generally associated with subjective distress or disability that occurs in an individual, and which are not a part of normal development or culture.

A disease of metabolism that has _material_basis_in enzyme deficiency or accumulation of enzymes or toxins which interfere with normal function due to an endocrine organ disease, organ malfunction, inadequate intake, dietary deficiency, or malabsorption.
An organ system cancer that is manifested in the reproductive organs.

A monogenic disease that is characterized by malformation of ectodermal (skin, hair, teeth and sweat glands) structures including hypotrichosis (sparseness of scalp and body hair), hypohidrosis (reduced ability to sweat), and hypodontia (congenital absence of teeth).
A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the thoracic cavity.
An organ system cancer that arises in the head or neck region. This region includes the nasal cavity, sinuses, lips, mouth, salivary glands, throat, or larynx.

A disease that is the consequence of the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, including pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and aberrant proteins known as prions.
A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the immune system.
A disease of anatomical entity that located_in the respiratory system which extends from the nasal sinuses to the diaphragm.
An organ system cancer located_in gastrointestinal tract that is manifested in organs of the gastrointestinal system.
A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the integumentary system comprising the skin and its appendages.
A disease of anatomical entity that occurs in the muscular and/or skeletal system.
A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in reproductive system organs.
A disease that has_material_basis_in a genetic abnormality, error with embryonic development, infection or compromised intrauterine environment.
A genetic disease that has_material_basis_in extra, missing, or re-arranged chromosomes.
An immune system disease that has material basis in abnormal immune responses.
An organ system cancer located_in endocrine system that is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of the hormone producing glands of the endocrine system.
A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in kidney, ureter, bladder and urethra.

An acquired metabolic disease that is characterized by an insufficient intake of food or of certain nutrients, by an inability of the body to absorb and use nutrients, or by overconsumption of certain foods.
A nervous system disease that affects the peripheral nervous system.
An immune system disease that results when one or more essential parts of the immune system is missing or not working properly at birth due to a genetic mutation.

A monogenic disease that is characterized by hypertelorism, hypospadias, and additional midline defects resulting from mutations to the MID1 gene in the X-linked form or from a deletion on chromosome 22q11.2 in the autosomal dominant form.
A disease of metabolism that is characterized by enzyme deficiency or accumulation of enzymes or toxins which interfere with normal function due to inherited enzyme abnormality.
